value.value: An invasive or non-invasive papillary transitional cell carcinoma of the urinary bladder. It is classified as low - or high-grade. -- 2003

label.value: micropapillary variant infiltrating bladder urothelial carcinoma

value.value: An infiltrating bladder transitional cell carcinoma exhibiting micropapillary growth pattern. -- 2003
A rare syndrome characterized by severe watery diarrhea, hypokalemia, and achlorhydria. It is caused by the oversecretion of vasoactive intestinal peptide from the pancreatic islet cells.
Pain or discomfort caused by exposure of the dentin layer of tooth to thermal, tactile, or other stimuli.

An epithelioid sarcoma involving the extremities. It usually presents as nodular masses in the dermis and subcutaneous tissues or in the tendons and fascia. It frequently recurs and metastasizes to other anatomic sites. The most common sites of metastasis are the lungs, lymph nodes, bones, and brain.
Uveal melanoma characterized by the presence of intermediate cells which are similar to but smaller than epithelioid cells.
Iris melanoma characterized by the presence of intermediate cells which are similar to but smaller than epithelioid cells.
A uveal melanoma that arises from the iris. It is the most common primary malignant neoplasm of the iris. The majority arise in preexisting nevi.
Choroid melanoma characterized by the presence of intermediate cells which are similar to but smaller than epithelioid cells.

label.value: intermediate cell type ciliary body melanoma

value.value: Ciliary body melanoma characterized by the presence of intermediate cells which are similar to but smaller than epithelioid cells.
An adenocarcinoma that arises from the gallbladder. It is characterized by the presence of extracellular mucin that constitutes more than fifty-percent of the tumor.

Diseases caused by abnormal function of the mitochondria. They may be caused by mutations, acquired or inherited, in mitochondrial dna or in nuclear genes that code for mitochondrial components. They may also be the result of acquired mitochondria dysfunction due to adverse effects of drugs, infections, or other environmental causes.
An astrocytoma, without designation of benign or malignant, that is found in the supratentorial region. The infratentorial location is more common in children.
A benign neoplasm of the ovary characterized by the presence of cystic structures lined by mucinous columnar epithelial cells in a fibrotic stroma.

A benign tumor, composed of lobules of mature adipocytes, that penetrates the surrounding tissue from which it arises. There is usually a higher local recurrence rate when compared with non-infiltrating lipomas.
A benign tumor, composed of mature adipocytes, that arises within the tendon sheath.
A benign well-circumscribed tumor, composed of lobules of mature adipocytes, that arises within the lumbosacral tissue of the spine.
An intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma that produces abundant mucin.
A benign adenomatous neoplasm that arises from the mucous glands in the bronchus.

A squamous cell carcinoma of the larynx that arises from the glottic area. It may remain localized for a long period then in late disease stage, it may spread to the opposite true vocal cord, supraglottic and subglottic areas, and the soft tissues of the neck. Hoarseness is the presenting symptom.

label.value: extrahepatic bile duct clear cell adenocarcinoma

value.value: A morphologic variant of extrahepatic bile duct adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelium composed of clear cells.
An immature teratoma that arises from the ovary and occurs in children.
A rare cutaneous lesion presenting as a scaly verrucous plaque. Morphologically, the plaque contains nests of basaloid cells.
A epithelioid cell melanoma that involves the optic choroid.
A epithelioid cell melanoma that involves the ciliary body.
A morphologic variant of large cell lung carcinoma characterized by the presence of a solid nodular or anastomotic trabecular growth pattern, peripheral palisading, and comedo type necrosis.
An aggressive variant of cervical squamous cell carcinoma characterized by the presence of nests of malignant basaloid squamous cells with scant amount of cytoplasm.

An aggressive, human papillomavirus-related squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the penis. It is characterized by the presence of nests of small malignant cells. The malignant cells tend to invade deeply into the adjacent tissues. Comedo-type necrosis is often present.
A squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the vulva and is characterized by the presence of nests of malignant basaloid cells with a scant amount of cytoplasm.
A basaloid squamous cell carcinoma that involves the zone of skin.

A rare primary thymic carcinoma, characterized by the presence of tumor cell lobules with peripheral palisading, and a basophilic staining pattern. More than half of reported cases were associated with the presence of a multilocular thymic cyst. Metastases to lung and liver have been reported in approximately 30% of cases.

A rare morphologic variant of esophageal squamous cell carcinoma. Histologically, it is composed of closely packed cells with hyperchromatic nuclei and scant basophilic cytoplasm. It has a similar prognosis to the conventional squamous cell carcinoma of the esophagus. (WHO)
Multiple meningiomas that affect the skull base.
A group of heterogeneous lymphoid tumors generally expressing one or more B-cell antigens or representing malignant transformations of B-lymphocytes.
A dermoid cyst that involves the spinal cord.

label.value: malignant melanocytic peripheral nerve sheath tumor of mediastinum

value.value: A rare variant of malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumor that arises from the mediastinum. It is characterized by the presence of malignant cells that contain melanin.
A cystic teratoma that occurs in an adult.

label.value: lung mixed small cell and squamous cell carcinoma

value.value: A lung carcinoma characterized by a combination of small cell carcinoma and squamous cell carcinoma.
A papillary carcinoma arising from the thyroid gland from multiple foci.

label.value: columnar cell variant thyroid gland papillary carcinoma

value.value: A morphologic variant of papillary carcinoma of the thyroid gland characterized by the presence of pseudostratified malignant follicular cells.

label.value: tall cell variant thyroid gland papillary carcinoma

value.value: A morphologic variant of papillary carcinoma of the thyroid gland characterized by the presence of tall malignant follicular cells, arranged in papillary and trabecular patterns. Necrotic changes and high mitotic activity are present.

label.value: splenic manifestation of hairy cell leukemia

value.value: A hairy cell leukemia that involves the spleen.
An epithelioid sarcoma occurring in childhood.

label.value: testicular yolk sac tumor, macrocystic pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of collections of thin-walled spaces.
A leukemia (disease) that involves the spleen.
A meningioma that affects the diaphragma sellae.
A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the epiglottis.
Hairy cell leukemia that is resistant to treatment.
A hematologic malignancy that is resistant to treatment.
